FROM THE ARCHIVES:
Transferring LPs & Cassettes to CD with Toast 5 Titanium

Probably the most-asked question we get here at the newsletter is
how to record old LPs and cassettes onto CD. Admit it, you've missed
listening to them, but are just too lazy to fire up the turntable, if
you even have one anymore. Whether you record your own albums, or your
parents' collection, you'll rediscover a wealth of good tunes in the
process. And the same technique can be applied to voice recordings.
Michael Murie tells you everything you need to know about transferring
your LPs and cassettes to CD with Toast 5 Titanium here.

http://roxio.chtah.com/a/tA$He5NAHsqQEALrCLPAHvX6bO7/rmac4

