      <p><font face=3D"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size=3D"2"><i>Q: I upg=
raded to=20
        Jaguar, but my SCSI CD recorder is no longer recognized. What's up?=
</i></font></p>
      <p><font face=3D"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size=3D"2">A: Toast 5.=
2 and above=20
        are fully compatible with Jaguar. An issue remains with CD Spin Doc=
tor=20
        where you cannot export directly to Toast via the Export button. In=
stead=20
        manually drag and drop your tracks from the CD Spin Doctor window d=
irectly=20
        into the Toast Audio window.</font></p>
      <p><font face=3D"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size=3D"2">In addition=
, Apple=20
        has made some changes in Jaguar that affect how SCSI drives are rec=
ognized.=20
        After installing Mac OS 10.2, it is possible the operating system w=
ill=20
        no longer see your drive as a CD recorder, only as CD player. Toast=
 depends=20
        on the driver information from the operating system to determine th=
e capabilities=20
        of a drive, and as such, will only see the drive as a CD player. Yo=
u will=20
        not be able to record discs with Toast. As this is a Mac OS 10.2 is=
sue,=20
        it affects recording through DiscBurner and iTunes as well. Apple h=
as=20
        released updates to Jaguar. In addition to other changes, they have=
 addressed=20
        some issues related to SCSI recorders, so be sure you have the late=
st=20
        version.</font><br>
